//axhos_step
. *Mint or Reuse Touchmark, and Compute the Present-Set (host-side)*:
.. Fresh capture: {rbbc_store}
`«TOUCHMARK»` as the kind-letter `«KIND»` + `YYMMDDHHMMSS` from current time (e.g. `vw260610095327`), with an empty present-set
.. Refresh (`--refresh «TOUCHMARK»`): reuse the supplied touchmark; read its existing `:rbi_vouch` envelope to derive the locked `«VERSION»` from any member's `rblv_origin`, then compute the PRESENT-SET from the GAR package's member tags — the source of truth, never the envelope alone — preserving each enveloped member verbatim and recovering each orphan tag (present in GAR, absent from the envelope after an interrupted prior run) with its digest from the tag's version reference and its `rblv_acquired_at` from that version's createTime
.. The host owns the touchmark so it — and thus the
{rbf_fact_lode}
path — is known before the build

